<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Circus_acrobatic> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#description> "A circus discipline with two distinct components: figures on the ground, where the acrobat uses his or her body to perform figures (contortions, jumps, balances, stunts, etc.) on the ground. This practice is similar to artistic gymnastics. Aerial acrobatics refers to all acrobatic exercises performed at height. Several aerial apparatus are used in this discipline, including the hoop, the corde lisse, the trapeze and the fabric." .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Circus_acrobatic> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-category-vocab/Sport> .
