<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Circus_equilibrium> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Circus_equilibrium> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Circus__> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Circus_equilibrium> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#description> "Balancing is the art of balancing. It involves performing technical feats by stabilising your body in incredible positions. The discipline can be performed with specific objects such as the balancing ball, stilts, the rolla bolla, the unicycle or the tightrope (funambulism)." .
