<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_African> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#description> "Refers to the various dance styles of sub-Saharan Africa. These dances are closely connected with the traditional rhythms and music traditions of the region. African dance uses the concepts of polyrhythm and total body articulation. African dances are a collective activity performed in large groups, with significant interaction between dancers and onlookers in the majority of styles" .
