<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_Kathak> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_Kathak> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_Kathak> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#description> " Kathak is one of the eight forms of classical Indian dance from northern India. It is primarily a form of theatre, with instrumental and vocal music and the use of stylised gestures and movements to represent the story being told. Its current form contains traces of Hindu temple dances and rituals, with influence from the bhakti movement" .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_Kathak> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-category-vocab/Sport> .
