<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_classical> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/source> "Dancefloor-Paris" .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_classical> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/ontology/Sport> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_classical> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_classical> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_classical> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#description> "A dance form that has evolved over the centuries to give rise to different styles such as Romantic and Neoclassical ballet. Classical dancers must master basic positions such as pliés, tendus and dégagés. Pointes, special shoes, allow dancers to dance on tiptoe, requiring exceptional balance, strength and flexibility" .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_classical> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-category-vocab/Sport> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_classical> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Dance classical" .
