<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_contemporary> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/ontology/Sport> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_contemporary> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_contemporary> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_contemporary> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#description> "A dance style focused on expression and improvisation, characterized by lighter, more fluid movements. This art form incorporates ballet techniques but is primarily influenced by modern dance, including floor movements, improvisation, and an aerial quality" .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Dance_contemporary> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-category-vocab/Sport> .
