<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/HIIT> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/source> "Wikipedia" .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/HIIT> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/ontology/Sport> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/HIIT> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/HIIT> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Anaerobic_exercise> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/HIIT> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#description> "Interval training aimed at improving physical conditioning through brief anaerobic exercise sessions. A workout consists of a warm-up period, approximately 6 to 10 repetitions of an exercise, and a cool-down period. Each exercise has two phases. The first phase is the intense effort phase, performed at the maximum intensity the practitioner is capable of. The second phase is the recovery phase, which can be either active (low to moderate intensity) or passive. The total duration of the session does not exceed half an hour. The ratio between effort and rest periods is typically 1:1." .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/HIIT> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-category-vocab/Sport> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/HIIT> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "HIIT" .
