<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Jiu-jitsu> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#description> "Ancestral Japanese martial art, grouping together combat techniques developed by the samurai to defend themselves when they were unarmed. These techniques are sometimes classified into five main categories: atemi-waza: striking techniques; nage-waza: throwing techniques; ne-waza: ground techniques; kansetsu-waza: arthralgic techniques (injuring joints); shime-waza: strangulation techniques; Kuatsu: ‘return to life’ or ‘resuscitation’ technique; Kyusho: technique of the vital points of the human body." .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Jiu-jitsu> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-category-vocab/Sport> .
