<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Karate> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#description> "Japanese martial art, although its origins are Okinawan. Karate is a martial art whose techniques aim to defend oneself and then respond with an attack targeting different parts of the body: fingers, open and closed hands, forearms, feet, elbows and knees. The fighter responds by defending or anticipating, known as Sendosei, which allows the attack to be made before the opponent's attack is made, followed by an attack in response to the opponent." .
