<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Precision_figure_skating> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Figure_skating> .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Precision_figure_skating> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#description> "Synchronized team skating, also known as precision skating, consists of a team of 8 or more skaters (in the United States) or 12 or more skaters (in Canada) who perform various movements, synchronized with at least part of the team. Skating elements include formations such as circles, lines, blocks, and wheels. Spirals are allowed, but jumps of more than one revolution are not. Lifts are also not permitted." .
<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Precision_figure_skating> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> <http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-category-vocab/Sport> .
