<http://ns.inria.fr/iadas/sport-vocab/Yoga_ashtanga> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#description> "Dynamic and demanding form of yoga that synchronizes breathing with a progressive series of postures. Ashtanga Is organised around six series of progressively demanding postures. These series are designed not only to strengthen the body but also to increase flexibility. Mysore practice, the hallmark of this discipline, emphasises students' independence while following a traditional pattern of movement." .
